Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Sasini of Kenya; Mumias Sugar Move

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-07-20T16:19:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-sasini-of-kenya-mumias-sugar-move.html
Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index fell for
the third day, declining 0.3 percent to 2,045.83 by the 1:30
p.m. close in  Port Louis , the lowest since April 20.  The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index gained for the
first day in three, advancing 0.7 percent to 23,707.47 by the
2:30 p.m. close in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement
from the bourse.  Namibia ’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  slid 0.3
percent to 842.63 by the 4 p.m. close in Windhoek. The Ghana
Stock Exchange Composite Index snapped two days of gains,
dropping 0.1 percent to 1,176.37 by the 3 p.m. close in Accra.
 Kenya ’s All-Share Index weakened 0.2 percent to 67.31 by the 3
p.m. close in Nairobi.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Mumias Sugar Co. (MSUG KN), Kenya’s biggest producer of the
sweetener, rose 10 cents, or 1.4 percent, to 7.30 shillings, the
highest since June 24, on speculation sugar prices will rise as
drought cuts production. The Kenya Sugar Board, which regulates
the nation’s industry, said yesterday it suspects traders are
hoarding supply to sell more expensively.  Sasini Ltd. (STCL)  , a Kenyan tea and coffee producer,
climbed 5 cents, or 0.5 percent, to 10.20 shillings, the highest
since July 15, after tea and top-grade coffee prices increased
at an auction yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
